==Content== Ley had written a number of books containing scientific oddities; ''Exotic Zoology'' collects the cryptozoological matter from those books.<ref>{{cite book|last=Bille|first=Matthew A.|title=Shadows of existence: discoveries and speculations in zoology|year=2006|publisher=Hancock House|isbn=978-0-88839-612-9|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sVYVAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Exotic+Zoology%22+%22willy+ley%22&dq=%22Exotic+Zoology%22+%22willy+ley%22&hl=en&ei=RkZITcXGEYnGgAeRm9DUBQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CDkQ6AEwBTge|page=216}}</ref> Throughout the book he shows examples of organisms that were rumored to exist, or were thought to be impossible, that were shown to be real; and others that were accepted as fact, that were discovered to have never existed: "He speculates about dragons and sea serpents, wingless birds and Abominable Snowmen."<ref>{{cite journal|title=Rev. of ''Exotic Zoology''|journal=[[Saturday Review (US magazine)|Saturday Review]]|year=1967|volume=50|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nC7oAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Exotic+Zoology%22+%22willy+ley%22&dq=%22Exotic+Zoology%22+%22willy+ley%22&hl=en&ei=t0VITZC8D8HegQfWg82JBg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDMQ6AEwAzgU|accessdate=1 February 2011|page=41}}</ref> The book, in its description of (fictional) peoples and creatures, has been compared to [[John Mandeville]]'s ''Travels''.<ref>{{cite book|last=Preece|first=Rod|title=Animals and nature: cultural myths, cultural realities|year=1999|publisher=UBC Press|isbn=978-0-7748-0724-1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GCcwJtu_qQQC&pg=PA277|page=277}}</ref> Some<!--understatement considering that one can't list every example--> of the claims have been criticized or ridiculed, for instance the statement that [[giant squid]]s had left scars on whales of two feet in diameter.<ref>{{cite book|last=Ellis|first=Richard|title=Monsters of the Sea|year=2006|publisher=Globe Pequot|isbn=978-1-59228-967-7|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nzfvYlO1hDcC&pg=PA252|page=252}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Ellis|first=Richard|title=The search for the giant squid|year=1999|publisher=Penguin|isbn=978-0-14-028676-2|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=70BQqBS2pJsC&q=%22Exotic+Zoology%22+%22willy+ley%22&dq=%22Exotic+Zoology%22+%22willy+ley%22&hl=en&ei=EUhITYm_HIbKgQfqn6DCBg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CEcQ6AEwCTgo|page=142}}</ref>
